# ============================================================
# park.dlg  —  Comprehensive example scene
# One file = one scene/view (the park).
# Each [interaction] is a separate dialogue graph.
# ============================================================

# Scene-wide background defaults.
# Any character listed here gets this bg unless overridden locally.
@bg Akihiko   bgAkihiko
@bg Yuki      bgYuki
@bg Hana      bgHana
@bg Merchant  bgShop
@bg Guard     bgGuard

== Scene: Riverside Park ==


# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 1 — Simple NPC, no choices
# Triggered when player walks up to the old man on the bench.
# ============================================================

[interaction: old_man | Old man sitting on the bench]

OldMan(bgBench): Hm? A visitor. Haven't seen one of those in a while.
OldMan(bgBench): This park used to be full of children, you know.
OldMan(bgBench): Now it's just me and the pigeons.
OldMan(bgBench): ...Anyway. Don't mind me. Enjoy the view.


# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 2 — Two characters, linear, bg switches mid-scene
# Akihiko finds Yuki reading by the fountain.
# ============================================================

[interaction: akihiko_meets_yuki | Akihiko finds Yuki at the fountain]

Akihiko: Hey — I thought that was you.
Yuki: Oh. Akihiko. You're the last person I expected to see here.
Akihiko: I could say the same. You actually left your room?
Yuki: Ha ha. Very funny.

# Background shifts to a closer shot of Yuki for emphasis
Yuki(bgYukiClose): I come here to think. The noise back home is… a lot.
Akihiko: Yeah. I get that.
Akihiko: I won't bother you then. Just wanted to say hi.
Yuki: ...You can stay. If you want.


# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 3 — Full branching dialogue with choices
# Player talks to Hana; she asks for help and the player decides.
# ============================================================

[interaction: hana_request | Hana asks the player for a favour]

Hana: Oh! You're here — perfect timing.
Hana: I've been trying to figure out where the flower market moved to.
Hana: I heard it's somewhere on the east side now, but I'm not sure.

Hana: Could you help me track it down?

[choice]
    > Sure, I'll look into it.  -> @hana_agree
    > Sorry, I'm busy right now -> @hana_decline
    > What's it worth to you?  -> @hana_negotiate

@hana_agree
Hana: Really? Thank you so much!
Hana: I need white peonies. The florist on Elm Street used to carry them.
Hana: I'll be at the north gate if you find anything.
[end]

@hana_decline
Hana: Oh… that's alright. I'll figure it out myself.
Hana(bgHanaSad): I always do.
[end]

@hana_negotiate
Hana: ...Ha. Direct. I like that.
Hana: How about this — I'll make you lunch if you find the place.

Hana: Deal?

[choice]
    > Deal.     -> @hana_deal_yes
    > No thanks -> @hana_decline

@hana_deal_yes
Hana: Perfect. I make excellent tamagoyaki, just so you know.
Hana: White peonies. North gate. Don't forget!
[end]


# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 4 — Three-way conversation, multiple characters
# The player stumbles into an argument between Yuki and the Guard.
# ============================================================

[interaction: yuki_guard_argument | Yuki arguing with a guard at the gate]

Guard: Ma'am, the east path is closed after sundown. I've said it twice.
Yuki: And I've told you — I left my bag on the bench. It will take thirty seconds.
Guard: Rules are rules. Come back tomorrow.

# Player arrives
Akihiko: Hey, what's going on?
Yuki: This guard won't let me through to get my bag.
Guard: Sir, please stay back. This doesn't concern you.

Akihiko: Can we work something out here?

[choice]
    > Vouch for Yuki     -> @vouch
    > Side with the guard -> @side_guard
    > Stay out of it      -> @stay_out

@vouch
Akihiko: I know her. She's not going to cause any trouble.
Guard: ...
Guard: Fine. Two minutes. And you're coming with her.
Yuki: Thank you.
Yuki(bgYukiClose): ...Both of you.
[end]

@side_guard
Akihiko: He's got a point, Yuki. Come back in the morning.
Yuki: Are you serious right now?
Yuki(bgYukiClose): Fine. Don't talk to me tonight.
[end]

@stay_out
Akihiko: Actually — yeah, none of my business. Carry on.
Guard: Smart man.
Yuki: Unbelievable.
[end]


# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 5 — Merchant with looping/conditional shop flavour
# A travelling merchant has a few things to say; ends with a jump.
# ============================================================

[interaction: merchant_greeting | Travelling merchant near the east gate]

Merchant: Welcome, welcome! Looking for anything in particular?
Merchant: I've got maps, dried goods, and a few… curiosities.

Merchant: What catches your eye?

[choice]
    > What kind of curiosities?  -> @merch_curious
    > Tell me about the maps.    -> @merch_maps
    > Just browsing, thanks.     -> @merch_bye

@merch_curious
Merchant: Ah, a person of taste!
Merchant(bgMerchantLean): I've got a compass that always points to your greatest regret.
Merchant: Terrible for navigation. Wonderful for drama.
Merchant: Interested?

[choice]
    > How much?   -> @merch_price
    > No thanks.  -> @merch_bye

@merch_price
Merchant: For you? Three silver.
Merchant: Or one favour. I'll let you decide which is cheaper.
[end]

@merch_maps
Merchant: Best maps this side of the river!
Merchant: I've got the eastern districts, old town routes, even the underground canals.
Merchant: The canal map's not strictly… legal to own. But that's between us.
[end]

@merch_bye
Merchant: No trouble at all. Come back anytime!
Merchant: I'll be here until the lanterns go out.
[end]


# ============================================================
# INTERACTION 6 — Brief sign / environmental dialogue
# A notice board. No character name needed — use "Sign" or "Narrator".
# ============================================================

[interaction: notice_board | Wooden notice board near the fountain]

Sign(bgBoard): [RIVERSIDE PARK — PUBLIC NOTICE]
Sign(bgBoard): The east footpath will be closed for maintenance from sundown.
Sign(bgBoard): Please use the north gate as an alternate route.
Sign(bgBoard): Thank you for your cooperation. — Park Authority
